    <title>Css Image Centering </title>

    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
            padding: 20px;
            background: #f5f5f5;
            max-width: 700px;
            margin: auto;
        }

        h2 {
            margin-top: 40px;
            color: #333;
        }
        .box {
            background: #fff;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 10px;
            margin-bottom: 30px;
        }

        /* 1 Method Margin:auto */
        .center-auto {
            display: block;
            margin: 0 auto;
            width: 250px;
            border-radius: 8px;
        }

        /* 2 Method Flexbox */
        .flex-center {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            height: 220px;
            background: #eaeaea;
            break-inside: 10px;
        }

        .flex-center img {
            width: 250px;
            border-radius: 8px;
        }

    </style>
</head>
<body>
    
    <h2>Method 1: margin:auto</h2>
    <div class="box">
        <p>Convert the image to a block element and give it auto side margins.</p>
        <img src="image/pc 1.jpg" alt="" class="center-auto">
    </div>

    <h2>Method 2: Flexbox</h2>
    <div class="box">
        <p>Wrap image in a flex container and center it horizontally (and vertically of needed)</p>
        <div class="flex-center">
            <img src="image/pc 2.jpg" alt="">
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
